label: CAN Bus Bridge
info:
Bridges CAN bus messages to local MQTT topics for the TrailCurrent PWA.

INBOUND: Subscribes to can/inbound, routes by CAN identifier, parses data,
and publishes to local/* topics (lights, air quality, GPS).

OUTBOUND: Subscribes to local/lights/*/command from the PWA and sends
CAN toggle/brightness messages to can/outbound.

SETUP:
1. Double-click any MQTT node, then click the pencil icon next to 'Local MQTT Broker'
2. Go to the Security tab and enter your MQTT username and password (from .env file)
3. Click Update, then click Deploy (red button, top right)

name: SETUP: Configure MQTT credentials in the broker node before deploying
info:
After importing this flow:
1. Double-click any MQTT node (e.g. 'CAN Inbound')
2. Click the pencil icon next to 'Local MQTT Broker'
3. Go to the Security tab
4. Enter your MQTT username and password (same values as MQTT_USERNAME / MQTT_PASSWORD in your .env file)
5. Click Update, then Deploy

The broker connects to the Mosquitto container via Docker internal DNS (mosquitto:8883).
TLS uses the self-signed CA certificate mounted at /data/ca.pem.

PWA Light Commands (local/lights/N/command -> CAN outbound)
info:
These nodes receive light toggle commands from the PWA backend
and convert them to CAN bus messages sent to can/outbound.

The PWA publishes to local/lights/{id}/command when a user taps a light button.
